    <script type="application/ld+json">
      {"@context":"http://schema.org","@graph":[{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"DiscussionForumPosting","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Tartu Rakenduslik Kolledž (Tartu Vocational College)","url":"https://ee.linkedin.com/company/tartu-voco"},"datePublished":"2026-05-12T13:15:35.242Z","headline":"","mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_tartuvoco-vocointernational-robotics-activity-7459954429618786304-kFT-","text":"🤖  It´s time to dance! \nWe are welcoming the first AgiBot X2 Ultra humanoid robot in the Baltics!\nThe new robot will soon support our vocational learners, offering invaluable hands-on experience in programming, maintenance, and modern robotics.\nThe collaboration between VOCO and AgiBot aims to bring world-class robotics directly to our students. By integrating this technology into our curriculum, we are opening new doors for international cooperation in this rapidly evolving field.\nRead more: \nhttps://lnkd.in/dKgKfhAA\n\n#tartuvoco #vocointernational #robotics #humanoid #agibot #engineering ","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_tartuvoco-vocointernational-robotics-activity-7459954429618786304-kFT-"},{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"DiscussionForumPosting","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Tartu Rakenduslik Kolledž (Tartu Vocational College)","url":"https://ee.linkedin.com/company/tartu-voco"},"datePublished":"2026-04-02T08:40:06.058Z","mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_tartuvoco-vocointernational-skillscompetition-activity-7445389586542944256-MR0-","text":"🏆 VOCO Shines at International Skills Competition in Riga!\nBig news from the international stage! From March 24–26, our talented students took part in the “Learn, Know, Do, Can, Show” skills competition in Riga, Latvia and the results were spectacular.\nWith 16 countries and 42 schools represented, VOCO stood among the best. \n🌟 Our Winners:\nSalesmanship: Berit Viigipuu (Mentor: Mariliis Maremäe)\nClassical Cooking: Eliis Sasmil (Mentors: Katrin Jurs, Kairi Timusk, Markus Pärn)\nVegan Culinary Art: Rannet Palmsaar (Mentors: Katrin Jurs, Kairi Timusk, Markus Pärn)\nConfectionery: Alexandra Aljaste (Mentor: Lilija Suburg)\nMeat Culinary: Tauri Koort (Mentor: Kristi Luht)\nMeat Culinary: Artem Danko (Mentor: Kamilla Lüdikainen)\nTourism: Pärle Punger (Mentor: Ene Reedi)\nA massive congratulations to all participants and a heartfelt thank you to the mentors who guided them to success. Your work truly matters! \n\n#tartuvoco  #vocointernational #SkillsCompetition #VocationalEducation #FutureTalent #LearnKnowDoCanShow #ProudMoment #ErasmusPlus","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_tartuvoco-vocointernational-skillscompetition-activity-7445389586542944256-MR0-"},{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"DiscussionForumPosting","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Tartu Rakenduslik Kolledž (Tartu Vocational College)","url":"https://ee.linkedin.com/company/tartu-voco"},"datePublished":"2026-03-25T15:45:46.935Z","mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_erasmusplus-clil-tartuvoco-activity-7442597609845714944-XGu6","text":"It’s time to welcome CLIL  and bring language lessons to kitchen! We have a great resource available: https://culinar.menu/\nIt is  a comprehensive toolkit designed specifically for the next generation of international chefs and hospitality professionals.\nWhat’s inside?\n ✅ The Illustrated Multilingual Gastronomy Dictionary: A visual guide to professional culinary terms. No more \"lost in translation\"—students can bridge the gap between 5 languages: English, Estonian, Latvian, Lithuanian, and Ukrainian.\n✅ 25 CLIL-Based Lessons: Expertly crafted modules that combine technical cooking skills with language acquisition.\n✅ Ready-to-Use Worksheets: Practical materials for teachers to download and implement in the classroom or kitchen immediately.\n\nLet´s boost culinary education and training! \n👉 Explore the resources here: https://culinar.menu/\n\nThis tool was made possible through the incredible collaboration of Rigas \nRīgas Tūrisma un radošās industrijas tehnikums (Latvia), VESK (Lithuania)\nChernivtsi High School of Commerce (Ukraine), Lviv Professional College of Hotel, Tourism and Restaurant Service (Ukraine) and Erasmus+programme. \n\n#ErasmusPlus #CLIL #tartuvoco #vocoprojects #vocointernational #CulinaryEducation #VocationalTraining #Multilingual #CulinaryArts #BoostingCulinaryEducation","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_erasmusplus-clil-tartuvoco-activity-7442597609845714944-XGu6"},{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"DiscussionForumPosting","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Tartu Rakenduslik Kolledž (Tartu Vocational College)","url":"https://ee.linkedin.com/company/tartu-voco"},"datePublished":"2026-03-19T09:17:20.978Z","mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_robintech-robotics-automation-activity-7440325530362576896-HicI","text":"Excited to share highlights from the Robintech collaborative seminar held at IES Bernat Guinovart!\nDuring this inspiring session, we explored the robotics teaching approaches and laboratories, visited AGFRA Automation Intelligence company to gain insight from industy. A key highlight was the hands-on seminar on robotics and automation, where we focused on programming Fanuc robots—an enriching experience bridging theory and real-world application.\nWe also introduced 5 new training module materials and engaged in meaningful discussions around their piloting and evaluation. These practical modules cover:\n• Welding robots\n• Machine vision\n• Connecting CNC and robots\n• Application of IO-Link in Industry\n• Getting started with EPLAN\nStay tuned for the new practical teaching resources about industrial robotics and automation! 🚀\n. \n#robintech #Robotics #Automation #vocoproject #vocointernational #ErasmusPlus #tartuvoco #rocmondriaan #forave #osao ","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_robintech-robotics-automation-activity-7440325530362576896-HicI"},{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"DiscussionForumPosting","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Tartu Rakenduslik Kolledž (Tartu Vocational College)","url":"https://ee.linkedin.com/company/tartu-voco"},"datePublished":"2026-03-04T09:02:10.483Z","mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_h2cove-greenskills4h2-hydrogen-activity-7434885893469085696-_Egb","text":"On 19 February, Tartu VOCO’s Engineering Academy hosted a professional training seminar titled “Teaching Hydrogen Technologies in Technical Vocational Education.” The event brought together vocational education and training (VET) teachers in technical fields from across Estonia.\n\nThe objective of the training was to strengthen teachers’ knowledge and practical readiness to integrate hydrogen technologies into their curricula and to discuss how vocational education can systematically prepare for the development of the hydrogen economy.\n\nThroughout the day, participants explored:\n✅ Fundamentals and safety aspects of hydrogen technologies\n✅ Practical teaching tools and simulations (Energy Box, Hydrogen stand)\n✅ Learning materials developed under the Green Skills for H2 initiative\n✅ Practical approaches for integrating hydrogen topics into different technical disciplines\n\nA key component of the training was a structured discussion on how to embed hydrogen-related competencies into automotive, energy, mechanical, and other technical study programmes in a consistent and sustainable manner.\n\nThe rapid evolution of the hydrogen value chain requires vocational education to adapt at the same pace. Empowering teachers with up-to-date knowledge and practical tools is essential to ensure high-quality, safe, and future-oriented professional training.\n\nWe thank all participants for their active engagement and valuable contributions, as well as the VOCO team for the excellent organisation of the event.\n\n#H2CoVE #GreenSkills4H2 #Hydrogen #VocationalExcellence #VET #TartuVOCO","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/posts/tartu-voco_h2cove-greenskills4h2-hydrogen-activity-7434885893469085696-_Egb"},{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"Organization","name":"Tartu Rakenduslik Kolledž (Tartu Vocational College)","url":"https://ee.linkedin.com/company/tartu-voco","address":{"type":"PostalAddress","streetAddress":"Kopli 1","addressLocality":"Tartu","postalCode":"50115","addressCountry":"EE"},"description":"Tartu Vocational College is the most versatile and leading education centre in Estonia offering a wide range of learning opportunities from pre-service and in-service education to training adolescents and adults. \nOur mission is to provide learning opportunities for masters to develop job skills for the future.\nWe offer tuition in Estonian language to a large and diverse target group of lifelong learners starting from age 16. We have more than 3000 students annually in vocational studies, as many grownups in professional courses. We provide the great opportunity to study more than 50 professions and practical skills in areas of IT, culinary, construction, business, technology, tourism and beauty as well as in-service trainings.","numberOfEmployees":{"value":148,"@type":"QuantitativeValue"},"logo":{"contentUrl":"https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C560BAQFNhUr6STzXEQ/company-logo_200_200/company-logo_200_200/0/1647600140911/tartu_voco_logo?e=2147483647&v=beta&t=D3PeeTvnkzOd7cGq8-9eq-EjKKnr2xZBciDmCeYcFxs","description":"Tartu Rakenduslik Kolledž (Tartu Vocational College)","@type":"ImageObject"},"slogan":"VOCO on Eesti suurim kutseõppekeskus. Siin on Sul vabadus avastada, eksida, valida ja areneda. VOCO-s õpid end vabaks!","sameAs":"http://voco.ee"}]}
    </script>
  
  
      
